      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): restore self-authored reply-media guard",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhen a bot replies to its own message that contains media, the reply handler tries to download and re-ingest that media. This causes incorrect agent behavior (the bot processes its own images as new inbound content).\n\nAdds a guard in the reply-media resolution path to skip media download when the replied-to message was authored by the bot itself.\n\nRebased onto current main (v2026.4.14).\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] Verified the guard is not present in upstream v2026.4.14\n- [x] `pnpm tsgo` passes",
